item.description:
Users are logical segmentations for end-users. It's a best practice to register users in order to have their information grouped and have control on both ends. It is required to have at least one user registered to create credentials


```json
{
    "id_user": "5e6686d1a8fcf0761318739f", 
    // SyncID, The ID of the User assignated by Paybook Sync
    "id_external": "ELSAN090909", 
    // String, The ID of the User assignated by Developer Application
    "name": "El Santo",
    // String, The name of the User
    "dt_create": 1583777489, 
    // Integer; a Unix timestamp of the time when the user was created
    "dt_modify": null 
    // Integer; a Unix timestamp of the time when the user was modified
}
```
